WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:34.503
Welcome to Grade 5 English, Unit 2: Exploring Space. Welcome to Unit 2! In this unit, you will explore the exciting world of space and discovery. You will read about how people study the stars, build amazing projects, and work together to achieve great things. Along the way, you will learn new vocabulary, practise important grammar skills, and develop your writing and speaking abilities. In this short lecture, preview the key ideas and prepare for the independent lesson.

2
00:00:34.583 --> 00:01:01.105
By the end of this unit, you will be able to use and understand 25 new vocabulary words related to systems, science, and social values. you will also identify and use indefinite pronouns such as everyone, somebody, nothing, and anything. you will also read and understand an informative passage about space exploration. Keep these goals in mind as you work.

3
00:01:01.185 --> 00:01:17.510
Your vocabulary work begins with these words: independence, issue, empire, expose, glare, source. Listen to each pronunciation in the vocabulary lab, study its meaning in context, and use the word accurately in your own discussion and writing.

4
00:01:17.590 --> 00:01:33.472
The reading sequence includes Exploring Space: source text 1 and Exploring Space: source text 2. Read actively. Identify each text's central ideas, notice viewpoint and reliability, and support every inference with relevant evidence from the text.

5
00:01:33.552 --> 00:02:04.951
The first language focus is What Are Indefinite Pronouns?. Indefinite pronouns are special words that we use when we want to talk about people or things in a general way, without being specific. They are called 'indefinite' because they do not point to a definite or particular person or thing. For example, instead of saying: Notice the structure in the model examples, then apply it deliberately in connected sentences and paragraphs.

6
00:02:05.031 --> 00:02:21.356
In speaking, you will complete Speaking 1: Astronaut Interview Role-Play. Organise your ideas, use evidence and respond clearly to questions. In writing, you will plan, draft, check and revise. Use the success criteria before submitting your work.

7
00:02:21.436 --> 00:02:39.534
You are ready to begin. Start with the vocabulary lab, continue through reading and comprehension, apply the grammar focus, and complete the speaking and writing practices. Use AI English for hints and feedback, and bring your questions to the live sessions.
